The paper discusses the use of automated techniques such as model checking to verify models of robotic mission plans based on Markov decision processes (MDPs) and generate counterexamples. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the sub-categories of Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI), Robotics (cs.RO), and Machine Learning (cs.LG). The paper also proposes an approach based on mixed-integer linear programming for generating explainable counterexamples, which suggests that it may also belong to the sub-categories of Software Engineering (cs.SE) and Programming Languages (cs.PL).
